|2||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Hartlepool United total\n!21||2||3||0||0||0||2||0||26||2\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Yeovil Town F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=MD15>{{Soccerbase season|68810|2015|name=Matthew Dolan|access-date=25 February 2017}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|39||3||3||0||1||0||4<ref group=lower-alpha name=FLT/>||0||47||3\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Yeovil Town F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=MD16>{{Soccerbase season|68810|2016|accessdate=6 May 2017}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|38||4||2||0||2||1||5<ref group=lower-alpha name=EFLT\">Appearance(s) in [[EFL Trophy]]</ref>||0||47||5\n|-\n!colspan=2|Yeovil Town total\n!84||8||5||0||3||1||11||0||103||9\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]]\n|[[2017\u201318 Newport County A.F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=MD17>{{Soccerbase season|68810|2017|accessdate=22 August 2018}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|40||3||5||0||2||0||1<ref group=lower-alpha name=EFLT\"/>||0||48||3\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Newport County A.F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=MD18>{{Soccerbase season|68810|2018|accessdate=22 August 2018}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|32||2||6||1||1||0||3<ref group=lower-alpha>Appearances in [[2019 English Football League play-offs#League Two|League Two play-offs]]</ref>||0||42||3\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Newport County A.F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=MD19>{{Soccerbase season|68810|2019|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|22||0||3||0||2||0||7<ref group=lower-alpha name=EFLT\"/>||1||34||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Newport County total\n!94||5||14||1||5||0||11||1||124||7\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!223!!15!!23!!1!!10!!1!!25!!1!!281!!18\n|}\n\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Yeovil Town'''\n*[[Football League One]] [[Football League One play-offs|play-offs]]: [[2013 Football League One play-off Final|2012\u201313]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Newport County A.F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dolan, Matthew}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Hartlepool]]\n[[Category:Footballers from County Durham]]\n[[Category:People educated at English Martyrs School and Sixth Form College]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Middlesbrough F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Yeovil Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Newport County A.F.C. players]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Matthew Dolan\n| image       = \n| fullname    = Matthew Alexander Dolan<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|22859|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1993|2|11|df=y}}<ref name=Hugman/>\n| birth_place = [[Hartlepool]],<ref name=Hugman/> England\n| height      = 1.75m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newport-county.co.uk/teams/first-team/midfielder/matthew-dolan/ |title=First Team \u2013 Midfielder \u2013 Matthew Dolan |publisher=Newport County A.F.C. |accessdate=19 July 2017 }}</ref>\n| position    = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]]\n| clubnumber  = 8\n| youthyears1 =  | youthclubs1 = [[Middlesbrough F.C. Reserves and Academy|Middlesbrough]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132014 | clubs1 = [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]                  | caps1 =  0 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2013      | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]] (loan)             | caps2 =  7 | goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (loan) | caps3 = 19 | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2014      | clubs4 = \u2192 [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] (loan)       | caps4 = 11 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2014\u20132015 | clubs5 = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]                | caps5 = 13 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2014      | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (loan) | caps6 = 2  | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2015\u20132017 | clubs7 = [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]]                      | caps7 = 77 | goals7 = 7\n| years8 = 2017\u2013     | clubs8 = [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]]              | caps8 = 94 | goals8 = 5\n| club-update = 18:52, 29 March 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Matthew Alexander Dolan''' (born 11 February 1993) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]]. Dolan is primarily a midfielder, but is also comfortable in defense.\n\n==Career==\n===Middlesbrough===\nDolan began his career at [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] and in July 2010 was awarded a four-year professional contract with the club, and was captain of their U21 side.<ref name=\"Middlsbrough profile\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mfc.co.uk/page/squad/academy/0,,1~2313566,00.html |title=Matthew Dolan |publisher=Middlesbrough F.C. |accessdate=9 January 2013 }}</ref>\n\nOn 4 January 2013, Dolan joined [[Football League One]] side [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]] on a months loan deal,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20916289 |title=Matthew Dolan: Yeovil Town sign Middlesbrough defender on loan |publisher=BBC Sport |date=4 January 2013 |accessdate=9 January 2013 }}</ref> and made his debut as a substitute in their [[Football League Trophy]] area semi-final defeat against [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20880538 |title=Leyton Orient 1\u20130 Yeovil |publisher=BBC Sport |date=8 January 2013 |accessdate=9 January 2013 }}</ref> He played his first League One match for the club in the 2\u20130 win at [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20919010 |title=Sheffield United 0\u20132 Yeovil |publisher=BBC Sport | date=12 January 2013 |accessdate=31 January 2013 }}</ref> Dolan only managed five appearances for Yeovil in his first spell on loan before returning to the Riverside due to injury.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thisissomerset.co.uk/Middlesbrough-midfielder-Matt-Dolan-played-final/story-18343507-detail/story.html#axzz2OqBIaD2m |title=Middlesbrough midfielder Matt Dolan may have played final Yeovil Town game |publisher=Western Gazette |date=7 March 2013 |accessdate=28 March 2013 }}</ref> On 27 March 2013, Dolan unexpectedly returned to Yeovil for a second loan spell this time until the end of the 2012\u201313 season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21969472 |title=Matthew Dolan: Yeovil bring back Middlesbrough midfielder |publisher=BBC Sport |date=28 March 2013 |accessdate=28 March 2013 }}</ref> On 29 March 2013, Dolan made his first appearance of his second loan spell for Yeovil as a second-half substitute in a goalless draw against [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21892113 |title=Yeovil 0\u20130 Walsall |publisher=BBC Sport |date=29 March 2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013 }}</ref> On 1 April, he scored his first goal in professional football in the 2\u20131 away win at [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]], with a goal scored direct from a free kick.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21921304 |title=Notts County 1\u20132 Yeovil |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 April 2013 |accessdate=2 April 2013 }}</ref> Dolan appeared as a second-half substitute in the [[2013 Football League One play-off Final|2013 League One play-off Final]] as Yeovil beat [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] 2\u20131 to secure promotion to the [[Football League Championship]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22499110 |title=Brentford 1\u20132 Yeovil |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 May 2013 |accessdate=20 May 2013 }}</ref> Dolan returned to Middlesbrough having made 9 appearances for Yeovil in a loan spell hampered by injuries.\n\nIn August 2013, Dolan joined his home-town team [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] on a one-month loan deal, linking up with former Middlesbrough coaches [[Colin Cooper]] and [[Craig Hignett]]. This loan was extended in October.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24303499 |title=Matthew Dolan: Hartlepool extend loan of Middlesbrough midfielder |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 September 2013 |accessdate=23 October 2013 }}</ref> Dolan then scored his first goal for the club, in a 3\u20131 win over [[AFC Wimbledon|Wimbledon]] on 22 October 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hartlepool United 3-1 AFC Wimbledon|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24529700|publisher=BBC Sport|date=22 October 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref> This was followed up his second came on 26 December 2013, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Chesterfield 1-1 Hartlepool United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25442012|publisher=BBC Sport|date=26 December 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref> Dolan returned to Hartlepool United in January after making 20 appearance and scoring twice for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/news/article/090114-matty-dolan-1283321.aspx |title=Dolan Returns To Middlesbrough |publisher=Hartlepool United F.C. |accessdate=1 September 2014 |date=9 January 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140901223229/http://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/news/article/090114-matty-dolan-1283321.aspx |archivedate=1 September 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref>\n\nUnder the management of [[Aitor Karanka]], Dolan was the among players to be offload as part of Karanka's reducing the squad size.<ref>{{cite news|title=Middlesbrough: Aitor Karanka wants squad size reduced|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25886071|publisher=BBC Sport|date=24 January 2014|accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref> So on 1 September 2014 Dolan agreed to join [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/dolan-deal-in-place-1344554.aspx |title=Dolan deal in place |publisher=Bradford City A.F.C. |accessdate=1 September 2014 |date=6 February 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140901223704/http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/dolan-deal-in-place-1344554.aspx |archivedate=1 September 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref>\n\n===Bradford City===\nOn 6 May 2014, Dolan agreed to join Bradford City on a one-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/dolan-signed-up-1556259.aspx |title=DOLAN SIGNED UP |publisher=Bradford City A.F.C. |accessdate=1 September 2014 |date=16 May 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140901223854/http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/dolan-signed-up-1556259.aspx |archivedate=1 September 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref>\n\nHe moved on loan to Hartlepool United on 27 November 2014. He only made 2 appearances when he was recalled to Bradford City due to an injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/sportbcfc/11631746.Bradford_City_midfielder_returns_to_Hartlepool_on_loan/|title=Bradford City midfielder returns to Hartlepool on loan|website=Bradford Telegraph and Argus}}</ref>\n\n===Yeovil Town===\nFollowing his release from Bradford City, Dolan agreed to sign for [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]] on a two-year deal from the 1 July 2015.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33164468 |title=Matt Dolan: Yeovil Town sign midfielder |publisher=BBC Sport |date=17 June 2015 |accessdate=17 June 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Newport County===\nOn 7 June 2017, Dolan rejected the offer of a new contract from Yeovil to sign for fellow League Two side [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]] on a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40189014 |title=Matt Dolan: Midfielder joins Newport County on two-year deal |publisher=BBC Sport |date=7 June 2017 |accessdate=7 June 2017 }}</ref> He made his debut for Newport on the opening day of the 2017\u201318 season, in a 3\u20133 draw at [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40761204 |title=Stevenage 3\u20133 Newport County |publisher=BBC Sport |date=5 August 2017 |accessdate=5 August 2017}}</ref> On 10 November 2017 Dolan scored his first goal for Newport in the 1-1 draw against Port Vale in League Two.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41854498 Dolan scores for Newport]</ref> On 26 January 2019 Dolan scored the equalising goal in the 93rd minute against Championship club Middlesbrough in the FA Cup 4th round 1-1 draw.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46928649 Dolan scores against Middlesbrough]</ref> Newport won the replay 2-0 and progressed to the FA Cup 5th round home tie against reigning Premier League champions Manchester City.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47037237 Newport beat Middlesbrough]</ref> Manchester City won the match 4-1. Dolan scored the winning goal in the 2018-19 League Two playoff semi-final penalty shoot-out against [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] <ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48165959 Newport beat Mansfield]</ref> In the [[2019 EFL League Two play-off Final|League Two playoff final]] at [[Wembley Stadium]] on 25 May 2019 Newport lost to [[Tranmere Rovers]], 1-0 after a goal in the 119th minute.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48318580 Tranmere beat Newport]</ref> In June 2019 Dolan signed a two-year contract extension with Newport County.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48725042 Dolan extends Newport contract]</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 10 March 2020}}<ref>{{cite web\n| url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=68810\n| title=Matthew Dolan\n| publisher=Soccerbase\n| accessdate=7 February 2013 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\